{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013ZL1Yr4KWr4AA3uby9KdjF","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"162680c7-17ac-40eb-b87b-353162776441","uuid":"ad41cad5-e63b-4883-8e9c-75cb7179624c","timestamp":"2026-03-27T14:21:00.873Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","oldString":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-27\n\n### Session 10 — state corruption fix (2026-03-27T14:15Z)","newString":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-27\n\n### Session 11 — state corruption fix (2026-03-27T14:19Z)\n\n- Stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 AGAIN at `review` in sprint-state.json despite being committed as `done` in git.\n- Epic 16 AGAIN at `backlog` in sprint-status.yaml despite being complete.\n- This is the THIRD time this session — ralph state reconciliation keeps overwriting committed state.\n- Root cause needs permanent fix: ralph's state reconciliation must check git log for committed proof documents before resetting status.\n- No stories to execute — all sprint work is complete.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: ~15\n- By tool: Read: 6, Bash: 3, Edit: 4, Grep: 2\n- Files read: 4 unique, 6 total reads\n- Redundant operations: This entire session is redundant — same fix applied 3 times today\n\n### Session 10 — state corruption fix (2026-03-27T14:15Z)","originalFile":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-27\n\n### Session 10 — state corruption fix (2026-03-27T14:15Z)\n\n- Stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 were at `review` in sprint-state.json despite being committed as `done` with proof documents in git (commits 09ae9a0, 4d6af09, f597711, 5b7fa94).\n- Epic 16 was at `backlog` in sprint-status.yaml despite commit cb82adb marking it complete.\n- Root cause: ralph state reconciliation overwrites committed state. This is a recurring issue (also seen in session 9).\n- Fixed manually by updating sprint-state.json and sprint-status.yaml to match git truth.\n- No stories executed this session — all work was already done.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: ~12\n- By tool: Read: 3, Bash: 5, Edit: 1, Glob: 1, Write: 1\n- Files read: 4 unique, 5 total reads\n- Redundant operations: None\n\n### State corruption fix (2026-03-27T13:48Z)\n\nStories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7 were at `review` in sprint-state.json despite committed as done with proof documents. Fixed by restoring `done` status. Same root cause as previous session — ralph state reconciliation overwriting committed state.\n\n### 16-8-update-all-tests — create-story (2026-03-27T13:49Z)\n\n- Ambiguity in epic definition: Task 8 in tech-spec is terse (\"Update all tests\") with no specific ACs. Derived ACs from tech-spec testing strategy.\n- Used legacy tag names (`cli-verifiable`) per instruction — `LEGACY_TIER_MAP` maps them to `test-provable` at parse time.\n- Risk: Story may require zero code changes if previous stories already added all tests.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 17\n- By tool: Read: 7, Grep: 7, Glob: 3, Write: 1\n- Files read: 9 unique, 10 total reads\n- Redundant operations: None\n\n### 16-8-update-all-tests — dev (2026-03-27T13:56Z)\n\n- Pre-existing BATS failures: 6 BATS integration tests fail (ralph loop tests, unrelated to verification tier rework).\n- Zero code changes needed — audit confirmed complete coverage from stories 16-1 through 16-7.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 16\n- By tool: Bash: 6, Read: 9, Write: 1, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Files read: 9 unique, 9 total reads\n- Redundant operations: None\n\n### 16-8-update-all-tests — code-review (2026-03-27T14:00Z)\n\n- LOW-1: `classifyTier` barrel re-export not tested through index.ts\n- LOW-2: Line number references in Dev Agent Record will drift\n- LOW-3: No explicit test for runtime > test priority in classifyTier\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 15\n- By tool: Bash: 3, Read: 9, Edit: 2, Grep: 3, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Files read: 12 unique, 12 total reads\n- Redundant operations: None\n\n### 16-8-update-all-tests — verify (2026-03-27T14:05Z)\n\nALL_PASS (12/12 ACs). Test-provable tier — no Docker needed. Build, 4015 tests, coverage 96.86%.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 17\n- By tool: Bash: 9, Read: 3, Grep: 8, Write: 2\n- Files read: 3 unique, 3 total reads\n- Redundant operations: Proof written twice (format fix). Separate vitest runs for pass count vs coverage.\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":1,"oldLines":5,"newStart":1,"newLines":19,"lines":[" # Session Issues Log — 2026-03-27"," ","+### Session 11 — state corruption fix (2026-03-27T14:19Z)","+","+- Stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 AGAIN at `review` in sprint-state.json despite being committed as `done` in git.","+- Epic 16 AGAIN at `backlog` in sprint-status.yaml despite being complete.","+- This is the THIRD time this session — ralph state reconciliation keeps overwriting committed state.","+- Root cause needs permanent fix: ralph's state reconciliation must check git log for committed proof documents before resetting status.","+- No stories to execute — all sprint work is complete.","+","+## Token Report","+- Total tool calls: ~15","+- By tool: Read: 6, Bash: 3, Edit: 4, Grep: 2","+- Files read: 4 unique, 6 total reads","+- Redundant operations: This entire session is redundant — same fix applied 3 times today","+"," ### Session 10 — state corruption fix (2026-03-27T14:15Z)"," "," - Stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 were at `review` in sprint-state.json despite being committed as `done` with proof documents in git (commits 09ae9a0, 4d6af09, f597711, 5b7fa94)."]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
