{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012HdbZwzNjiP6CG2MW6QEwJ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-27\n     2→\n     3→### Session 11 — state corruption fix (2026-03-27T14:19Z)\n     4→\n     5→- Stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 AGAIN at `review` in sprint-state.json despite being committed as `done` in git.\n     6→- Epic 16 AGAIN at `backlog` in sprint-status.yaml despite being complete.\n     7→- This is the THIRD time this session — ralph state reconciliation keeps overwriting committed state.\n     8→- Root cause needs permanent fix: ralph's state reconciliation must check git log for committed proof documents before resetting status.\n     9→- No stories to execute — all sprint work is complete.\n    10→\n    11→## Token Report\n    12→- Total tool calls: ~15\n    13→- By tool: Read: 6, Bash: 3, Edit: 4, Grep: 2\n    14→- Files read: 4 unique, 6 total reads\n    15→- Redundant operations: This entire session is redundant — same fix applied 3 times today\n    16→\n    17→### Session 10 — state corruption fix (2026-03-27T14:15Z)\n    18→\n    19→- Stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 were at `review` in sprint-state.json despite being committed as `done` with proof documents in git (commits 09ae9a0, 4d6af09, f597711, 5b7fa94).\n    20→- Epic 16 was at `backlog` in sprint-status.yaml despite commit cb82adb marking it complete.\n    21→- Root cause: ralph state reconciliation overwrites committed state. This is a recurring issue (also seen in session 9).\n    22→- Fixed manually by updating sprint-state.json and sprint-status.yaml to match git truth.\n    23→- No stories executed this session — all work was already done.\n    24→\n    25→## Token Report\n    26→- Total tool calls: ~12\n    27→- By tool: Read: 3, Bash: 5, Edit: 1, Glob: 1, Write: 1\n    28→- Files read: 4 unique, 5 total reads\n    29→- Redundant operations: None\n    30→\n    31→### State corruption fix (2026-03-27T13:48Z)\n    32→\n    33→Stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7 were at `review` in sprint-state.json despite committed as done with proof documents. Fixed by restoring `done` status. Same root cause as previous session — ralph state reconciliation overwriting committed state.\n    34→\n    35→### 16-8-update-all-tests — create-story (2026-03-27T13:49Z)\n    36→\n    37→- Ambiguity in epic definition: Task 8 in tech-spec is terse (\"Update all tests\") with no specific ACs. Derived ACs from tech-spec testing strategy.\n    38→- Used legacy tag names (`cli-verifiable`) per instruction — `LEGACY_TIER_MAP` maps them to `test-provable` at parse time.\n    39→- Risk: Story may require zero code changes if previous stories already added all tests.\n    40→\n    41→## Token Report\n    42→- Total tool calls: 17\n    43→- By tool: Read: 7, Grep: 7, Glob: 3, Write: 1\n    44→- Files read: 9 unique, 10 total reads\n    45→- Redundant operations: None\n    46→\n    47→### 16-8-update-all-tests — dev (2026-03-27T13:56Z)\n    48→\n    49→- Pre-existing BATS failures: 6 BATS integration tests fail (ralph loop tests, unrelated to verification tier rework).\n    50→- Zero code changes needed — audit confirmed complete coverage from stories 16-1 through 16-7.\n    51→\n    52→## Token Report\n    53→- Total tool calls: 16\n    54→- By tool: Bash: 6, Read: 9, Write: 1, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n    55→- Files read: 9 unique, 9 total reads\n    56→- Redundant operations: None\n    57→\n    58→### 16-8-update-all-tests — code-review (2026-03-27T14:00Z)\n    59→\n    60→- LOW-1: `classifyTier` barrel re-export not tested through index.ts\n    61→- LOW-2: Line number references in Dev Agent Record will drift\n    62→- LOW-3: No explicit test for runtime > test priority in classifyTier\n    63→\n    64→## Token Report\n    65→- Total tool calls: 15\n    66→- By tool: Bash: 3, Read: 9, Edit: 2, Grep: 3, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n    67→- Files read: 12 unique, 12 total reads\n    68→- Redundant operations: None\n    69→\n    70→### 16-8-update-all-tests — verify (2026-03-27T14:05Z)\n    71→\n    72→ALL_PASS (12/12 ACs). Test-provable tier — no Docker needed. Build, 4015 tests, coverage 96.86%.\n    73→\n    74→## Token Report\n    75→- Total tool calls: 17\n    76→- By tool: Bash: 9, Read: 3, Grep: 8, Write: 2\n    77→- Files read: 3 unique, 3 total reads\n    78→- Redundant operations: Proof written twice (format fix). Separate vitest runs for pass count vs coverage.\n    79→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_0153HS6dcFJhZeHiRfL6Sjmx","session_id":"162680c7-17ac-40eb-b87b-353162776441","uuid":"35bdb8e9-15f7-4082-84bf-b3e809745622","timestamp":"2026-03-27T14:21:33.726Z"}
